{
  "doc_id": "17681",
  "text": "Panobinostat (LBH589) is a potent, small-molecule inhibitor of class I, II, and IV HDACs that was FDAapproved for the treatment of multiple myeloma [CITATION_1] . Panobinostat shows antitumor and antiangiogenic effects in glioma. A phase II trial of panobinostat in combination with bevacizumab in recurrent GBM was well tolerated. However, the trial was terminated because combination regimen did not significantly improve PFS at 6 month compared to historical controls of bevacizumab monotherapy (NCT00859222) [CITATION_2] .",
